						<div class="postbody">Addressable tile count isn't too much of a problem if you have VRAM and aren't trying to scroll as fast as <em>Sonic the Hedgehog 2</em> in Chemical Plant 2. Just replace the tiles themselves along the seam. This might require a 248-pixel-wide window to cut off the wrap tile at left and right, but nobody complained when Kirby Super Star used a 248.<br /><br />But 4-bit works when you can divide the pic into areas that use different sets of 15 colors.</div>

