						<div class="postbody">I'm under the impression that in the early days, &quot;fast&quot; ROM rated at 120 ns was more expensive than &quot;slow&quot; ROM rated at 200 ns. Nowadays costs are different, but I'm still curious how much optimization could have been done without just saying &quot;screw it; let's just OC the ROM.&quot;</div>

